  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, in the extensions metadata, we have random data used by different tools for different purposes, it would not be relevant/performant to make it all available for searching.\r\n\r\nWe should only limit this to the metadata fields which are relevant to be searched from in a `key:value` way:\r\n`status:stable,experimental`, `xxx-support:supported`, `origin:platform`, `origin:other`, `category:web`, `category:web,data`, `xxx-support:any`, `extra:codestart`\r\n\r\nPossible filter values would be `any` (exists),  or some specific value (i.e `xxx-support:any` would check that the field is defined to any value)\r\n\r\nWe should keep a way to search in all the values (like we currently do with `tags:...` in code.quarkus.io): `tags:platform,supported` \r\n\r\nMaybe we should just be stupid and \"hardcode\" the list of available fields in the devtools (and make it evolve): \r\n```\r\norigin, *-support, category, status, extra, keywords\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe would also need a way to list the available fields and values to be used for searching.\r\n\r\n`origin` and `extra` don't exist yet and would need to be added.\r\n\r\n",
